text: Omphalea triandra, also known as Jamaican cobnut and pop nut is a plant species endemic to Jamaica and Haiti.Encyclopædia Britannica Larvae of certain species of moths of the genus Urania feed on the leaves of Omphalea triandra.Texas Entomology - Urania Natural History ==References== ==External links== * Category:Acalyphoideae Category:Flora of Jamaica
